<html>
  <head>
    <style>
      body {
        background: MediumPurple;
        font-family: sans-serif;
      }
    </style>
    <!-- <link rel='stylesheet' type='text/css' href='../public/index.css'/> -->
  </head>

  <body>
    <h2><strong>WELCOME TO YOUR TO DO LIST</strong></h2>
    <p>You can use this application to manage your to do list, by:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>adding a todo action</li>
        <li>editing a todo action</li>
        <li>marking an action as completed</li>
      </ul>
    <p>You can also view all your stored actions, as well as view which are completed, and which are oustanding.</p>

    <h4>Use the todo list application below:</h4>

    <form>
      <input type='text' name='add_item' />
      <input type='submit' value='Add an action' />
    </form>

    <p>
      <em style="color: navy; font-size: 0.8em;">Note: all actions are automatically input as active. Once completed you can update them using complete an action below</em>
    </p>

    <form>
      <input type='text' name='find' placeholder='name of action' />
      <input type='text' name='edit' placeholder='change to'  />
      <input type='submit' value="Edit an action"/>
    </form>

    <form>
      <input type='text' name='complete' placeholder='mark as complete'/>
      <input type='submit' value="Complete an action"/>
    </form>

    <form>
      <p>
        Filter list by: <input type='submit' name="display_all" value="All"/><input type='submit' name="display_active" value="Active"/><input type='submit' name="display_complete" value="Completed"/>
      </p>
    </form>

    <h4><strong>Here is your filtered ToDo List:</strong></h4>
    <p><%= pp display_list %></p>

  </body>

</html>
